cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper presents a multiple-person tracking algorithm that uses particle filters and crowd models to predict pedestrian motion. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the algorithm can be applied to robot navigation in crowded environments. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the algorithm uses online learning to estimate internal goals of tracked pedestrians. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the algorithm uses particle filters to aggregate multiple predictions from different time steps. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category, but still possible as the algorithm can be applied to control systems for crowd management.
